Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["KnoodleDraw", "ObjectName",ExpressionUUID->"3ae41734-de6a-4d5d-b950-585d0f6f1242"],

Cell[TextData[{
 Cell["   ", "ModInfo",ExpressionUUID->"721934f4-adce-4580-816e-40f21df618dd"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"KnoodleDraw", "[", 
   StyleBox["input", "TI"], "]"}]], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "220a3b83-44d6-41cd-87a6-4a3a45339a8f"],
 "\[LineSeparator]draws a picture of a knot or link diagram, returning a \
Graphics object."
}], "Usage",ExpressionUUID->"d69b108e-bbe1-40f6-8828-6c7a899ea214"],

Cell["\<\
input may be a KnotData specification (e.g. Knot[3,1], {3,1}, or \
\"Trefoil\"), a PD/DTCode/GaussCode from the KnotTheory package, a Function \
(sampled as a closed space curve for t from 0 to 2 Pi), a list of 3D points \
(one closed space curve), a list of point lists (a multi-component link), a \
native Knoodle PD code, or a PlanarDiagramComplex from KnoodleSimplify.\
\>", "Notes",ExpressionUUID->"58546dc3-d39b-44b2-944c-a0a4931039db"],

Cell["\<\
A native Knoodle PD code is a list of crossing rows of 4 to 7 integers each: \
4 columns give an unsigned PD code, a 5th column gives the crossing \
handedness (\[PlusMinus]1), and two further columns carry the incoming \
under-/over-arc component colors that keep link components identified through \
simplification. A list of such row lists denotes a connect sum or split link, \
one summand each; the empty summand {} is an unknot, so {{}} draws the \
standalone unknot.\
\>", "Notes",ExpressionUUID->"259e786f-f40f-41a6-baec-5d1303560e1f"],

Cell["\<\
3D geometry and KnotData inputs are simplified before drawing by default; \
explicit diagram inputs (PD codes, KnotTheory objects, PlanarDiagramComplex) \
are drawn exactly as given unless \"Simplify\" -> True is set.\
\>", "Notes",ExpressionUUID->"dfb0a204-5a56-44bd-a444-3f5a50e3d548"],

Cell["\<\
KnoodleDraw returns Graphics, or Legended[Graphics, \[Ellipsis]] when \
PlotLegends -> Automatic is given. When the input yields several diagrams (a \
multi-summand PlanarDiagramComplex, a connect sum, or a split link), it \
returns a list of Graphics drawn at one common scale: the widest drawing gets \
the requested ImageSize and the others are proportionally smaller, so \
strands, gaps, arrowheads, and label text are the same physical size across \
the whole output. Unrecognized input yields $Failed with a \
KnoodleDraw::badinput message.\
\>", "Notes",ExpressionUUID->"aa894d73-9a9b-41e8-b34c-1431ecb3ece3"],

Cell["\<\
Labels are set in Source Sans Pro at the largest size at which every label \
fits its allotted space, uniformly across all diagrams of the output. \
LabelStyle styles the label text (family, weight, color, \[Ellipsis]); its \
directives merge on top of the default, and a font family that is not \
actually installed will fall back silently with possibly mismatched label \
sizing. A numeric FontSize inside LabelStyle is honored only when no explicit \
ImageSize is given, and then sets the overall drawing scale; label placement \
is not configurable.\
\>", "Notes",ExpressionUUID->"5cddbab7-dc4f-4480-a15e-ca62b3f74226"],

Cell["The following options can be given:", "Notes",ExpressionUUID->"1f9f7d45-6b95-4918-aa8a-d15b6343abef"],

Cell[BoxData[GridBox[{
   {Cell["      ", "ModInfo",ExpressionUUID->
     "adbf478c-1861-4412-af1a-2396fcc55543"], "\"\<Simplify\>\"", "Automatic",
     Cell["\<\
whether to simplify the diagram before drawing; Automatic simplifies \
geometry/KnotData input but draws explicit diagram input as-is\
\>", "TableText",ExpressionUUID->"ddd39636-e8ce-4d23-907c-ad28369ac063"]},
   {Cell["      ", "ModInfo",ExpressionUUID->
     "0d6b7744-74a6-43ea-bcce-365e49aa2969"], "\"\<Thickness\>\"", 
    "Automatic", Cell["\<\
strand thickness: Automatic scales with the diagram so crossing gaps stay \
visible (capped at 7 pt); a number is an AbsoluteThickness in points, clamped \
to the same proportional bound; any other directive is used as-is\
\>", "TableText",ExpressionUUID->"7ad5f3fc-27b6-411e-9e80-339738d2c4ec"]},
   {Cell["      ", "ModInfo",ExpressionUUID->
     "5c183bae-7776-4a86-82f0-91a196aca644"], "\"\<Checkerboard\>\"", "False",
     Cell["shade the diagram's two-colorable faces", "TableText",
     ExpressionUUID->"a79fc2bd-7292-4586-bec3-e29cfcf724a5"]},
   {Cell["      ", "ModInfo",ExpressionUUID->
     "daf6a0d0-73f9-4a84-8dfa-8f87599f9790"], "\"\<Orientation\>\"", "False", 
    Cell["\<\
True marks each arc's orientation with arrowheads along the strand (two per \
grid square of run)\
\>", "TableText",ExpressionUUID->"06e73793-da35-4fa1-b3cb-e0ae4a0e0d12"]},
   {Cell["      ", "ModInfo",ExpressionUUID->
     "991b8372-09d9-465c-8fe0-a0c053ac168c"], "\"\<Labels\>\"", 
    RowBox[{"{", "}"}], Cell["\<\
annotate 0-based element ids: a subset of {\"Crossings\", \"Arcs\", \
\"Faces\"}. Arc labels are set into the strand, once per grid square of run\
\>", "TableText",ExpressionUUID->"b34ba8a1-b053-488f-835e-5c89f4ade62d"]},
   {Cell["      ", "ModInfo",ExpressionUUID->
     "78ff425f-6299-4ddf-96e6-e710513c935d"], "LabelStyle", 
    RowBox[{"{", "}"}], Cell["\<\
styles the label text (font family, weight, color, \[Ellipsis]); merged over \
the default Source Sans Pro. Label size and placement are computed and not \
configurable, except that a FontSize given without an explicit ImageSize sets \
the overall drawing scale\
\>", "TableText",ExpressionUUID->"ed68d86c-3d84-4ff5-9fbc-7e48a993d412"]},
   {Cell["      ", "ModInfo",ExpressionUUID->
     "a7da20ca-b682-4ba4-afe4-3576e5043c4b"], "\"\<ExteriorFace\>\"", 
    "Automatic", Cell["\<\
which face (0-based id) to lay out as the unbounded exterior region\
\>", "TableText",ExpressionUUID->"ca90ea17-e48f-4faf-b3f7-60be1da9bab9"]},
   {Cell["      ", "ModInfo",ExpressionUUID->
     "8c3ea663-657b-4b36-b510-1c72208a50d8"], "PlotLegends", "None", 
    Cell["\<\
Automatic adds a LineLegend matching component colors to component numbers\
\>", "TableText",ExpressionUUID->"e4f0cee6-ee74-4b04-8dcb-255d8e350843"]},
   {Cell["      ", "ModInfo",ExpressionUUID->
     "18af4c16-8ecc-4320-9eb2-b130342cf007"], "\"\<RandomizeProjection\>\"", 
    "True", Cell["\<\
randomly rotate 3D input before projecting, avoiding degenerate projections; \
set False for reproducibility\
\>", "TableText",ExpressionUUID->"7b563f95-5f95-46cb-9c8b-603c1051528e"]},
   {Cell["      ", "ModInfo",ExpressionUUID->
     "f0ef0d82-5cc2-4c8d-ba48-be673c965b4e"], "\"\<LayoutOptions\>\"", 
    RowBox[{"{", "}"}], Cell["\<\
extra knoodledraw layout flags, e.g. {\"randomize-bends\" -> 3}; see \
knoodledraw --help\
\>", "TableText",ExpressionUUID->"ea3bc403-a0f4-451d-bdc5-8e1c21f3a5f2"]},
   {Cell["      ", "ModInfo",ExpressionUUID->
     "dc7dfb59-e8e9-471e-9e7e-8a31636de969"], "ImageSize", "340", Cell["\<\
size of the resulting Graphics; with several diagrams, the size of the widest \
(the rest are proportionally smaller, at a common scale)\
\>", "TableText",ExpressionUUID->"dccc2e21-8834-445f-bbcb-3d2028b6b455"]}
  }]], "3ColumnTableMod",ExpressionUUID->"c6f9bcd1-cdb0-4b13-99ce-\
782f7ccf7f66"]
}, Open  ]],

